    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1943-09-12T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1943-09-12T00:00:00-05:00" n="33"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d33">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">
                    <persName corresp="#p_RFD1">Roosevelt</persName> Papers: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">Marshal <persName corresp="#p_SIV1" type="from"
                            >Stalin</persName> to President <persName corresp="#p_RE1" type="to"
                            >Roosevelt</persName> and Prime Minister <persName corresp="#p_CC2"
                            >Churchill</persName>
                    </hi>
                    <note n="1" xml:id="d33fn1">Apparently sent via the Soviet Embassy, Washington.
                        The entire document is printed in <hi rend="italic">
                            <persName corresp="#p_SIV1">Stalin</persName>’s Correspondence</hi>,
                        vol. <hi rend="smallcaps">ii</hi>, p. 93.</note>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">[<placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Moscow</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1943-09-12">September 12,
                            1943</date>.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p rend="center">Translation</p>
                <p>Personal and secret message from Premier <persName corresp="#p_SIV1">I. V.
                        Stalin</persName> to President <persName corresp="#p_RFD1">Franklin D.
                        Roosevelt</persName> and Prime Minister <persName corresp="#p_CWS1">Winston
                        Churchill</persName> I have received your messages of September 10th.<note
                        n="2" xml:id="d33fn2">
                        <persName corresp="#p_RFD1">Roosevelt</persName>’s message referred to here
                        is presumably the one sent from Washington September 9, 1943, <hi
                            rend="italic">ante</hi>, <ref target="#pg_24">p. 24</ref>. <persName
                            corresp="#p_CC2">Churchill</persName>’s is that of September 10, 1943,
                        printed in <persName corresp="#p_CC2">Churchill</persName>, p. 281.</note>
                </p>
                <p rend="center">. . . . . . . . . . . . . .</p>
                <p>3. As to the meeting of the heads of the three Governments, I do not have any
                    objections regarding Tegeran [<hi rend="italic">Tehran</hi>] as the place of the
                    meeting, which (Tegeran) is more appropriate than Egypt where the Soviet Union
                    does not have its representation.</p>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">September</hi> 12, 1943.</p>
            </div>
        </body>
